      <ResourceName>Helios2 - E3 - magnetic field 6-sec average</ResourceName>
      <ReleaseDate>2020-08-18T16:18:19Z</ReleaseDate>
      <Description>
            The instrument is a dual configuration of two tri-axial fluxgate magnetometers
            operating at four different sensitivities (from 0.84 to 0.03 nT).
            The time resolution, depending the operation mode, telemetry format, and 
            bit rate, for most cases varied from 0.07 to 1.5 seconds.
            
            The present data set contains six-second averages of the magnetic field
            elements in solar-ecliptic (SE) spacecraft-centered coordinates.
            Data are stored in files on a daily basis.
</Description>
